\begin_layout Abstract
In this paper, we study dynamics of geodesic flows over closed surfaces
 of genus greater than or equal to 2 without focal points.
 Especially, we prove that there is a large class of potentials having unique
 equilibrium states, including scalar multiples of the geometric potential,
 provided the scalar is less than 1.
 Moreover, we discuss ergodic properties of these unique equilibrium states.
 We show these unique equilibrium states are Bernoulli, and weighted regular
 period orbits are equidistributed relative to these unique equilibrium
 states.
\end_layout

