\begin_layout Standard
This paper is devoted to the study of dynamics of the geodesic flows over
 closed surfaces without focal points.
 We focus on the thermodynamics of the geodesic flows, especially, the uniquenes
s of the equilibrium states and their ergodic properties.
 For uniform hyperbolic flows, also known as Anosov flows, thanks to fundamental
 works of Ruelle, Bowen, and Ratner, we know that every 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

H
\backslash
"{o}lder
\end_layout

\end_inset

 potential has a unique equilibrium state which enjoys several ergodic features
 such as possessing Bernoulli and equidistribution properties.
 It is also well-known that the geodesic flow on a negatively curved manifold
 is uniformly hyperbolic.
 However, when the manifold contains subsets with zero or positive curvature,
 the geodesic flow becomes non-uniformly hyperbolic.
 The non-uniform hyperbolicity greatly increases the difficulty in understanding
 the thermodynamics of these flows.
 Nevertheless, the geometric features of surfaces without focal points bring
 us hopes to investigate the dynamics of their geodesic flows.
 There are several geometric properties are available in this setting such
 as the flat strip theorem, 
\begin_inset Formula $C^{2}$
\end_inset

-regularity of the horocycles, and more.
 These properties enable us to derive and extend the existence of unique
 of measure of maximal entropy
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Knieper:1998ht"

\end_inset

 and the equilibrium state 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "BCFT2017"

\end_inset

 on closed rank 1 nonpositively curved manifolds to closed surfaces without
 focal points and genus at least 2.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Combining the dynamical and geometric features of surfaces without focal
 points, in this paper, we are able to prove the uniqueness of equilibrium
 states for a large class of potentials and Bernoulli and equidistribution
 properties for such equilibrium states.
 These results also generlize Gelfert-Ruggiero's recent work 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Gelfert:2017tx"

\end_inset

 on the uniqueness of measure of the maximum entropy for the geodesics flows
 over surfaces without focal points.
\end_layout

