 For surfaces without focal points, we can describe the singular set as
 
\begin_inset Formula $\Sing=\{v\in T^{1}S:\ K(\pi f_{t}v)=0\ \forall t\in\R\}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi:T^{1}S\to S$
\end_inset

