The second result, following Theorem A, we discuss several ergodic properties
 of these unique equilibrium states.
 We successfully extend several properties known to hold under uniform hyperboli
c cases (cf., for example, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Parry:1990tn"

\end_inset

), as well as under nonpositively curved surfaces (cf., for example, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Pollicott:1996jq"

\end_inset

